headline: Kayak CEO on $457 Million Writedown: Google Squeezed the Travel Industry Again
summary: Google has been downplaying free organic links for many years. In the past year, its AI Overviews and other ad formats have basically forced travel companies to spend more for traffic. Kayak isn't the only player feeling the squeeze.

headline: Stock Market Today: Dow Ends Lower As Traders Slash Rate-Cut Bets; Nvidia Holds To $5 Trillion Mark
summary: The Dow Jones Industrial Average finished in the red in Wednesday's mixed close after Federal Reserve Chair Jerome Powell said there's no certainty of another 2025 cut in interest rates.  Nvidia, however, held to higher ground in the stock market today, locking its place as Wall Street's first company to close with a $5 trillion valuation.  The chip designer's shares rose ahead of earnings reports from three fellow Magnificent Seven companies.

headline: Stock Market Today: Dow Falls As Powell Says December Cut Not Certain; Nvidia Higher (Live Coverage)
summary: The Dow Jones Industrial Average and other stock indexes turned lower Wednesday afternoon as Federal Reserve Chair Jerome Powell cast doubt on whether policymakers are locked in for another rate cut this year after November's reduction.  Stocks were higher after the Fed cut its key rate by 25 basis points but drifted downward during Powell's afternoon press conference.  The Dow fell 0.4% after briefly touching the 48,000 level for the first time.

headline: BKNG Q3 Deep Dive: Loyalty, AI Features, and Direct Bookings Drive Growth Amid Margin Pressures
summary: Online travel agency Booking Holdings (NASDAQ:BKNG) reported Q3 CY2025 results topping the market’s revenue expectations, with sales up 12.7% year on year to $9.01 billion. Its GAAP profit of $84.40 per share was 10% below analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: Agoda Data Reveals Top Honeymoon Destinations for Indian Travelers in 2025
summary: Digital travel platform Agoda's latest data on the most searched honeymoon destinations reveals Indian newlyweds are chasing sunsets, islands, and immersive experiences. Goa continues to reign as the top domestic choice, while Dubai leads internationally. The surprise of the year: Vietnam's Phu Quoc Island has seen an eightfold increase in popularity, entering the top ten rank for the first time.
